<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,153,395]" pageId="8" pageNumber="288">
A male specimen was designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[651,749,189,215]" pageId="8" pageNumber="288">holotype</typeStatus>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Murayama, S. &amp; Okamura, H." box="[792,1139,189,215]" pageId="8" pageNumber="288" pagination="10 - 25" refId="ref6180" refString="Murayama, S. &amp; Okamura, H. (1973) Butterflies of Luzon Island in Philippines, with descriptions of new species and subspecies. Tyo to Ga, 24 (1), 10 - 25." type="journal article" year="1973">Murayama &amp; Okamura (1973)</bibRefCitation>
, and the specimen was retrieved in 
<collectionCode box="[265,326,225,251]" country="Japan" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/pcbg-hhf5" name="Lake Biwa Museum" pageId="8" pageNumber="288">LBM</collectionCode>
(
<figureCitation box="[341,477,224,251]" captionStart="FIGURES 37–45" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1965,1990]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,1029,1935]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,1029,1940]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 37–45. 37–39. Carterocephalus dieckmanni soyosanus Murayama, 1983, holotype; 40–42. Sebastonyma suthepiana Murayama &amp; Kimura, 1990, holotype; 43–45. Halpe nuydai Murayama &amp; Okamura, 1973, holotype. Scale bar = 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3990963" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3990963/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="288">Figs. 43–45</figureCitation>
; Dried Insect Database Reg. no. 1500022031).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,153,395]" pageId="8" pageNumber="288">
Though 
<bibRefCitation author="Murayama, S. &amp; Okamura, H." box="[294,640,261,287]" pageId="8" pageNumber="288" pagination="10 - 25" refId="ref6180" refString="Murayama, S. &amp; Okamura, H. (1973) Butterflies of Luzon Island in Philippines, with descriptions of new species and subspecies. Tyo to Ga, 24 (1), 10 - 25." type="journal article" year="1973">Murayama &amp; Okamura (1973)</bibRefCitation>
claimed that the genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murayama &amp; Okamura" authorityYear="1973" box="[972,1048,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Halpe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nuydai">
<emphasis box="[972,1048,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="288">nuydai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembled that of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Matsumura, 1910)" baseAuthorityName="Matsumura" baseAuthorityYear="1910" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Thoressa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horishana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="288">Thoressa horishana</emphasis>
(Matsumura, 1910)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[495,580,297,323]" name="Taiwan" pageId="8" pageNumber="288">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, they somehow classified 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murayama &amp; Okamura" authorityYear="1973" box="[870,946,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Halpe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nuydai">
<emphasis box="[870,946,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="288">nuydai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Moore, 1878" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1878" box="[1093,1315,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Halpe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1093,1161,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="288">Halpe</emphasis>
Moore, 1878
</taxonomicName>
. The taxon was synonymized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kawazoe, A." box="[393,581,333,359]" pageId="8" pageNumber="288" pagination="91 - 98" refId="ref5719" refString="Kawazoe, A. (1973) A revisional note on some Philippine Lycaenidae and Hesperiidae reported by Murayama and Okamura. Tyo to Ga, 24 (4), 91 - 98." type="journal article" year="1973">Kawazoé (1973)</bibRefCitation>
, and we follow his treatment. 
<taxonomicName authority="Murayama &amp; Okamura, 1973" authorityName="Murayama &amp; Okamura" authorityYear="1973" box="[920,1410,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Halpe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nuydai">
<emphasis box="[920,1072,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="288">Halpe nuydai</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Murayama, S. &amp; Okamura, H." box="[1079,1410,333,359]" pageId="8" pageNumber="288" pagination="10 - 25" refId="ref6180" refString="Murayama, S. &amp; Okamura, H. (1973) Butterflies of Luzon Island in Philippines, with descriptions of new species and subspecies. Tyo to Ga, 24 (1), 10 - 25." type="journal article" year="1973">Murayama &amp; Okamura, 1973</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Inoue &amp; Kawazoe, 1969" authorityName="Inoue &amp; Kawazoe" authorityYear="1969" box="[505,967,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Thoressa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="justini">
<emphasis box="[505,684,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="288">Thoressa justini</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Inoue, S. &amp; Kawazoe, A." box="[691,967,369,395]" pageId="8" pageNumber="288" pagination="380 - 383" refId="ref5638" refString="Inoue, S. &amp; Kawazoe, A. (1969) A new Hesperiid butterfly found in Luzon belonging to the hitherto unrecorded genus from the Philippines: Thoressa Swinhoe (Lepidoptera). Kontyu, 37, 380 - 383." type="journal article" year="1969">Inoué &amp; Kawazoé, 1969</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
